President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Stephanie Sanders Sullivan as Ambassador to the Republic of the Congo, and Joseph Y. Yun as Ambassador to Malaysia. He has also announced his intent to appoint Avril D. Haines as Deputy Director of the Central Intelligence Agency, and Michael J. Morell as a member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board. Stephanie Sanders Sullivan is currently Chief of Staff for the Office of the Deputy Secretary of State for Management and Resources, and Joseph Y. Yun is currently Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and Pacific Affairs. Avril D. Haines is currently Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Counsel to the President for National Security Affairs, and Michael J. Morell is currently Deputy Director of the Central Intelligence Agency.